get.description: Provide the Post-Incident Review (PIR) document of a specified service issue for tenant.  An issue only with status of PostIncidentReviewPublished indicates that the PIR document exists for the issue. The operation returns an error if the specified issue doesn't exist for the tenant or if PIR document does not exist for the issue.

Retrieve the properties and relationships of a serviceHealthIssue object. This operation retrieves a specified service health issue for tenant. The operation returns an error if the issue does not exist for the tenant.

Provide the Post-Incident Review (PIR) document of a specified service issue for tenant.  An issue only with status of PostIncidentReviewPublished indicates that the PIR document exists for the issue. The operation returns an error if the specified issue doesn't exist for the tenant or if PIR document does not exist for the issue.

edge.description: A container for Microsoft Edge resources. Read-only.

microsoft365Apps.description: A container for the Microsoft 365 apps admin functionality.

people.description: Represents a setting to control people-related admin settings in the tenant.

reportSettings.description: A container for administrative resources to manage reports.

serviceAnnouncement.description: A container for service communications resources. Read-only.

internetExplorerMode.description: A container for Internet Explorer mode resources.

siteLists.description: A collection of site lists to support Internet Explorer mode.

allOf.title: browserSiteList

description.description: The description of the site list.

displayName.description: The name of the site list.

lastModifiedBy.description: The user who last modified the site list.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The date and time when the site list was last modified.

publishedBy.description: The user who published the site list.

publishedDateTime.description: The date and time when the site list was published.

revision.description: The current revision of the site list.

sharedCookies.description: A collection of shared cookies defined for the site list.

sites.description: A collection of sites defined for the site list.

allOf.description: A singleton entity which is used to specify IE mode site list metadata

allOf.title: browserSite

allowRedirect.description: Controls the behavior of redirected sites. If true, indicates that the site will open in Internet Explorer 11 or Microsoft Edge even if the site is navigated to as part of a HTTP or meta refresh redirection chain.

createdDateTime.description: The date and time when the site was created.

deletedDateTime.description: The date and time when the site was deleted.

history.description: The history of modifications applied to the site.

lastModifiedBy.description: The user who last modified the site.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The date and time when the site was last modified.

allOf.description: Singleton entity which is used to specify IE mode site metadata

comment.description: The comment for the shared cookie.

createdDateTime.description: The date and time when the shared cookie was created.

deletedDateTime.description: The date and time when the shared cookie was deleted.

history.description: The history of modifications applied to the cookie.

hostOnly.description: Controls whether a cookie is a host-only or domain cookie.

lastModifiedBy.description: The user who last modified the cookie.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The date and time when the cookie was last modified.

installationOptions.description: A container for tenant-level settings for Microsoft 365 applications.

itemInsights.description: Represents administrator settings that manage the support for item insights in an organization.

profileCardProperties.description: Contains a collection of the properties an administrator has defined as visible on the Microsoft 365 profile card.

pronouns.description: Represents administrator settings that manage the support of pronouns in an organization.

disabledForGroup.description: The ID of a Microsoft Entra group, of which the specified type of insights are disabled for its members. The default value is null. Optional.

isEnabledInOrganization.description: true if insights of the specified type are enabled for the organization; false if insights of the specified type are disabled for all users without exceptions. The default value is true. Optional.

annotations.description: Allows an administrator to set a custom display label for the directory property and localize it for the users in their tenant.

directoryPropertyName.description: Identifies a profileCardProperty resource in Get, Update, or Delete operations. Allows an administrator to surface hidden Microsoft Entra ID properties on the Microsoft 365 profile card within their tenant. When present, the Microsoft Entra ID field referenced in this property is visible to all users in your tenant on the contact pane of the profile card. Allowed values for this field are: UserPrincipalName, Fax, StreetAddress, PostalCode, StateOrProvince, Alias, CustomAttribute1,  CustomAttribute2, CustomAttribute3, CustomAttribute4, CustomAttribute5, CustomAttribute6, CustomAttribute7, CustomAttribute8, CustomAttribute9, CustomAttribute10, CustomAttribute11, CustomAttribute12, CustomAttribute13, CustomAttribute14, CustomAttribute15.

isEnabledInOrganization.description: true to enable pronouns in the organization; otherwise, false. The default value is false, and pronouns are disabled.

displayConcealedNames.description: If set to true, all reports conceal user information such as usernames, groups, and sites. If false, all reports show identifiable information. This property represents a setting in the Microsoft 365 admin center. Required.

healthOverviews.description: A collection of service health information for tenant. This property is a contained navigation property, it is nullable and readonly.

issues.description: A collection of service issues for tenant. This property is a contained navigation property, it is nullable and readonly.

messages.description: A collection of service messages for tenant. This property is a contained navigation property, it is nullable and readonly.

service.description: The service name. Use the list healthOverviews operation to get exact string names for services subscribed by the tenant.

issues.description: A collection of issues that happened on the service, with detailed information for each issue.

feature.description: The feature name of the service issue.

featureGroup.description: The feature group name of the service issue.

impactDescription.description: The description of the service issue impact.

isResolved.description: Indicates whether the issue is resolved.

posts.description: Collection of historical posts for the service issue.

service.description: Indicates the service affected by the issue.

actionRequiredByDateTime.description: The expected deadline of the action for the message.

attachmentsArchive.description: The zip file that contains all attachments for a message.

hasAttachments.description: Indicates whether the message has any attachment.

isMajorChange.description: Indicates whether the message describes a major update for the service.

services.description: The affected services by the service message.

tags.description: A collection of tags for the service message. Tags are provided by the service team/support team who post the message to tell whether this message contains privacy data, or whether this message is for a service new feature update, and so on.

viewPoint.description: Represents user viewpoints data of the service message. This data includes message status such as whether the user has archived, read, or marked the message as favorite. This property is null when accessed with application permissions.

allowedDomainGuidsForSyncApp.description: Collection of trusted domain GUIDs for the OneDrive sync app.

availableManagedPathsForSiteCreation.description: Collection of managed paths available for site creation. Read-only.

deletedUserPersonalSiteRetentionPeriodIn.description: The number of days for preserving a deleted user's OneDrive.

excludedFileExtensionsForSyncApp.description: Collection of file extensions not uploaded by the OneDrive sync app.

idleSessionSignOut.description: Specifies the idle session sign-out policies for the tenant.

imageTaggingOption.description: Specifies the image tagging option for the tenant. Possible values are: disabled, basic, enhanced.

isCommentingOnSitePagesEnabled.description: Indicates whether comments are allowed on modern site pages in SharePoint.

isFileActivityNotificationEnabled.description: Indicates whether push notifications are enabled for OneDrive events.

isLegacyAuthProtocolsEnabled.description: Indicates whether legacy authentication protocols are enabled for the tenant.

isLoopEnabled.description: Indicates whether if Fluid Framework is allowed on SharePoint sites.

isMacSyncAppEnabled.description: Indicates whether files can be synced using the OneDrive sync app for Mac.

isRequireAcceptingUserToMatchInvitedUser.description: Indicates whether guests must sign in using the same account to which sharing invitations are sent.

isResharingByExternalUsersEnabled.description: Indicates whether guests are allowed to reshare files, folders, and sites they don't own.

isSharePointMobileNotificationEnabled.description: Indicates whether mobile push notifications are enabled for SharePoint.

isSharePointNewsfeedEnabled.description: Indicates whether the newsfeed is allowed on the modern site pages in SharePoint.

isSiteCreationEnabled.description: Indicates whether users are allowed to create sites.

isSiteCreationUIEnabled.description: Indicates whether the UI commands for creating sites are shown.

isSitePagesCreationEnabled.description: Indicates whether creating new modern pages is allowed on SharePoint sites.

isSitesStorageLimitAutomatic.description: Indicates whether site storage space is automatically managed or if specific storage limits are set per site.

isSyncButtonHiddenOnPersonalSite.description: Indicates whether the sync button in OneDrive is hidden.

isUnmanagedSyncAppForTenantRestricted.description: Indicates whether users are allowed to sync files only on PCs joined to specific domains.

personalSiteDefaultStorageLimitInMB.description: The default OneDrive storage limit for all new and existing users who are assigned a qualifying license. Measured in megabytes (MB).

sharingAllowedDomainList.description: Collection of email domains that are allowed for sharing outside the organization.

sharingBlockedDomainList.description: Collection of email domains that are blocked for sharing outside the organization.

sharingCapability.description: Sharing capability for the tenant. Possible values are: disabled, externalUserSharingOnly, externalUserAndGuestSharing, existingExternalUserSharingOnly.

sharingDomainRestrictionMode.description: Specifies the external sharing mode for domains. Possible values are: none, allowList, blockList.

siteCreationDefaultManagedPath.description: The value of the team site managed path. This is the path under which new team sites will be created.

siteCreationDefaultStorageLimitInMB.description: The default storage quota for a new site upon creation. Measured in megabytes (MB).

tenantDefaultTimezone.description: The default timezone of a tenant for newly created sites. For a list of possible values, see SPRegionalSettings.TimeZones property.

id.description: The unique identifier for an entity. Read-only.

application.description: Optional. The application associated with this action.

device.description: Optional. The device associated with this action.

user.description: Optional. The user associated with this action.

microsoft.graph.browserSiteHistory.title: browserSiteHistory

allowRedirect.description: Controls the behavior of redirected sites. If true, indicates that the site will open in Internet Explorer 11 or Microsoft Edge even if the site is navigated to as part of a HTTP or meta refresh redirection chain.

compatibilityMode.description: Controls what compatibility setting is used for specific sites or domains. The possible values are: default, internetExplorer8Enterprise, internetExplorer7Enterprise, internetExplorer11, internetExplorer10, internetExplorer9, internetExplorer8, internetExplorer7, internetExplorer5, unknownFutureValue.

lastModifiedBy.description: The user who last modified the site.

mergeType.description: The merge type of the site. The possible values are: noMerge, default, unknownFutureValue.

publishedDateTime.description: The date and time when the site was last published.

targetEnvironment.description: The target environment that the site should open in. The possible values are: internetExplorerMode, internetExplorer11, microsoftEdge, configurable, none, unknownFutureValue.Prior to June 15, 2022, the internetExplorer11 option would allow opening a site in the Internet Explorer 11 (IE11) desktop application. Following the retirement of IE11 on June 15, 2022, the internetExplorer11 option will no longer open an IE11 window and will instead behave the same as the internetExplorerMode option.

isMicrosoft365AppsEnabled.description: Specifies whether users can install Microsoft 365 apps on their MAC devices. The default value is true.

isSkypeForBusinessEnabled.description: Specifies whether users can install Skype for Business on their MAC devices running OS X El Capitan 10.11 or later. The default value is true.

isMicrosoft365AppsEnabled.description: Specifies whether users can install Microsoft 365 apps, including Skype for Business, on their Windows devices. The default value is true.

isProjectEnabled.description: Specifies whether users can install Microsoft Project on their Windows devices. The default value is true.

isSkypeForBusinessEnabled.description: Specifies whether users can install Skype for Business (standalone) on their Windows devices. The default value is true.

isVisioEnabled.description: Specifies whether users can install Visio on their Windows devices. The default value is true.

displayName.description: If present, the value of this field is used by the profile card as the default property label in the experience (for example, 'Cost Center').

localizations.description: Each resource in this collection represents the localized value of the attribute name for a given language, used as the default label for that locale. For example, a user with a nb-NO client gets 'Kostnadssenter' as the attribute label, rather than 'Cost Center.'

details.description: More details about service event. This property doesn't support filters.

endDateTime.description: The end time of the service event.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: The last modified time of the service event.

startDateTime.description: The start time of the service event.

title.description: The title of the service event.

createdDateTime.description: The published time of the post.

description.description: The content of the service issue post. The supported value for the contentType property is html.

postType.description: The post type of the service issue historical post. Possible values are: regular, quick, strategic, unknownFutureValue.

contentType.description: The type of the content. Possible values are text and html.

isArchived.description: Indicates whether the user archived the message.

isFavorited.description: Indicates whether the user marked the message as favorite.

isRead.description: Indicates whether the user read the message.

isEnabled.description: Indicates whether the idle session sign-out policy is enabled.

signOutAfterInSeconds.description: Number of seconds of inactivity after which a user is signed out.

warnAfterInSeconds.description: Number of seconds of inactivity after which a user is notified that they'll be signed out.

displayName.description: The display name of the identity.For drive items, the display name might not always be available or up to date. For example, if a user changes their display name the API might show the new value in a future response, but the items associated with the user don't show up as changed when using delta.

id.description: Unique identifier for the identity or actor. For example, in the access reviews decisions API, this property might record the id of the principal, that is, the group, user, or application that's subject to review.

displayName.description: If present, the value of this field contains the displayName string that has been set for the language present in the languageTag field.

languageTag.description: Provides the language culture-code and friendly name of the language that the displayName field has been provided in.
